<*,*,*,*>: The ornithopter design reflects Leonardo’s study of avian anatomy and biomechanics. The mechanism involves manual wing articulation, likely via a pulley system. While impractical for sustained flight, the design represents an early instance of biomimicry and engineering foresight.
